[1] Cholera - Angola (Uige Province)
Date: Mon 1 Jan 2018
Source: SAPO 24 [machine trans. edited]
http://24.sapo.pt/atualidade/artigos/surto-de-colera-ja-fez-cinco-mortos-na-cidade-angolana-do-uige


An outbreak of cholera has killed 5 people in the Angolan province of Uige, which has been plagued by an outbreak of the disease since last week, government officials said. According to the governor of the Uíge province, Mpinda Simão, in addition to a malaria outbreak, the province now faces cases of cholera, already confirmed by the health authorities. "In addition to malaria, the cholera epidemic has arisen. At first, we were not sure; the technicians did their work; we received confirmation that the cases of diarrhea that we have here in the province are linked to cholera," said Mpinda Simão in statements issued by Angolan public radio.

The secretary of state for public health, José Vieira Dias da Cunha, who went to that northern province of Angola to assess the situation, said that there is a need for improvement in basic sanitation and distribution of drinking water to avoid these situations. "It is very important that we all know that cholera is a disease that has a lot to do with environmental sanitation and the distribution of drinking water. If these 2 issues are properly resolved, it is difficult for a population to contract this type of disease," he stressed.

The cholera epidemic is affecting the 3 main neighborhoods of the city of Uíge, according to health authorities.

