[5] Cholera - Kenya (Busia County)
Date: Tue 26 Dec 2017
Source: KBC [edited]
http://www.kbc.co.ke/local-news/cholera-outbreak-claims-5-lives-busia/


Health officials in Busia County are on high alert following an outbreak of cholera that has claimed 5 lives.

20 people are receiving treatment at the Teso North Sub County referral hospital, Kocholya. The patients, who had been exhibiting vomiting and diarrhea symptoms, are believed to have contracted the deadly bacterial disease after consuming food at a party engagement in Uganda before crossing back to the country. They were complaining of stomach pains, vomiting, and diarrhea.

According to medical officials in the area, more than 29 people with similar cases had been treated, with the outbreak expected to escalate due to deficient sanitation and lack of access to clean drinking water in the area.

Teso North Sub County public health officer Dr Kelvin Tangara says 4 cases tested positive for cholera.

[byline: Lynace Mwashighadi]

